 all $x_0\\in \\mathbb{R}^k\\backslash \\mathcal{E}_2$, any cluster\npoint of the sequence $x_{n+1}=H(x_n)$ is not a saddle point, and more\ngenerally cannot be an isolated generalised saddle point.\n  Some other results are proven.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Nov 2019 12:58:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Nov 2019 12:54:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-14"}
